#: axiom.config.load_config:1 of
msgid "Load configuration from the settings file."
msgstr "Charge la configuration depuis le fichier de réglages."

#: axiom.config.load_config:3 of
msgid ""
"Returns sensible defaults if the file does not exist or is malformed. "
"Never raises. The result is cached as long as the file's mtime does not "
"change (`save_config` goes through the file: automatic invalidation)."
msgstr ""
"Retourne des défauts raisonnables si le fichier n'existe pas ou est "
"malformé. Ne lève jamais. Le résultat est mis en cache tant que le mtime "
"du fichier ne change pas (`save_config` passe par le fichier : "
"invalidation automatique)."

#: ../../api/config.md
msgid "Returns"
msgstr "Renvoie"

#: axiom.config.load_config:7 of
msgid "AppConfig populated from disk, or a default AppConfig on any error."
msgstr ""
"AppConfig peuplé depuis le disque, ou un AppConfig par défaut en cas "
"d'erreur."

#: axiom.config.save_config:1 of
msgid "Persist an AppConfig to the settings file."
msgstr "Persiste un AppConfig dans le fichier de réglages."

#: axiom.config.save_config:3 of
msgid "Creates the config directory if it does not exist."
msgstr "Crée le dossier de configuration s'il n'existe pas."

#: axiom.config.save_config:5 of
msgid "The configuration to save."
msgstr "La configuration à enregistrer."

#: ../../api/config.md
msgid "Raises"
msgstr "Lève"

#: axiom.config.save_config:7 of
msgid "If the file cannot be written (propagated to the caller)."
msgstr "Si le fichier ne peut pas être écrit (propagée à l'appelant)."

#: axiom.config.resolve_extraction_model:1 of
msgid "Pick the model name for auxiliary LLM calls (hero decision, extraction)."
msgstr ""
"Choisit le nom du modèle pour les appels LLM auxiliaires (décision du "
"héros, extraction)."

#: axiom.config.resolve_extraction_model:3 of
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"`extraction_model` is an Ollama-style local model name; it only makes "
"sense for the universal/Ollama backend. On a cloud backend (Gemini, "
"Claude, Venice, Fireworks, OpenAI) there is no separate local model, so "
"sending `extraction_model` (\"llama3.1:8b\") to the provider yields a "
"404. Fall back to the provider's main model in that case."
msgstr ""
"`extraction_model` est un nom de modèle local façon Ollama ; il n'a de "
"sens que pour le backend universal/Ollama. Sur le backend Gemini il n'y a"
" pas de modèle local séparé, donc envoyer `extraction_model` "
"(\"llama3.1:8b\") à l'API Gemini donne un 404. Dans ce cas, repli sur le "
"`gemini_model` configuré."

#: axiom.config.resolve_time_model:1 of
msgid "Return the correct time model identifier based on the active backend."
msgstr "Retourne l'identifiant correct du modèle de temps selon le backend actif."

#: axiom.config.resolve_time_model:3 of
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"On a cloud backend the local time_model identifier cannot be used, so we "
"fall back to the provider's main model."
msgstr ""
"Si le backend est Gemini, l'identifiant local time_model est "
"inutilisable, donc repli sur le gemini_model."

#: axiom.config.memory_mode_is_living:1 of
msgid "True when living memory (LLM fact extraction) is enabled for this config."
msgstr ""

#: axiom.config.memory_mode_is_living:3 of
msgid ""
"Defensive: any value other than the explicit \"living\" opt-in (typos, "
"legacy blanks, unknown strings) resolves to the safe offline \"lite\" "
"mode, so the LLM is never engaged by accident."
msgstr ""

#: axiom.config.memory_beliefs_active:1 of
msgid "True when evolving beliefs (Phase 3 consolidation) should run."
msgstr ""

#: axiom.config.memory_beliefs_active:3 of
msgid ""
"Requires living memory AND the explicit beliefs opt-in, so the extra "
"consolidation LLM pass never fires in lite mode or without the toggle."
msgstr ""

#: axiom.config.memory_mental_models_active:1 of
msgid "True when curated mental models (§7.8) should be built and injected."
msgstr ""

#: axiom.config.memory_mental_models_active:3 of
msgid ""
"Requires evolving beliefs (a model is distilled *from* beliefs) AND the "
"explicit mental-models opt-in, so this extra LLM pass never fires without"
" both."
msgstr ""

#: axiom.config.build_llm_from_config:1 of
msgid "Instantiate and return the correct LLMBackend for the given config."
msgstr "Instancie et retourne le bon LLMBackend pour la config donnée."

#: axiom.config.build_llm_from_config:3 of
msgid "The current AppConfig."
msgstr "L'AppConfig courant."

#: axiom.config.build_llm_from_config:4 of
msgid "Optional model identifier to use instead of the default."
msgstr "Identifiant de modèle optionnel à utiliser à la place du défaut."

#: axiom.config.build_llm_from_config:6 of
msgid "A concrete LLMBackend instance ready for use."
msgstr "Une instance concrète de LLMBackend prête à l'emploi."

